    <properties>
        <title>Gaderian Downloads</title>
    </properties>
    <body>
        <section name="Maven 2">

            <p>The Gaderian releases are all available from the Maven Central repository, so no new repository settings are required to use Gaderian in your project.</p>
            <p>To use Gaderian modules within your Maven 2 enabled project, simply add the following dependencies of the modules of Gaderian that you wish to use:</p>
            <source><![CDATA[
                    <dependencies>
                        ...
                        <dependency>
                         <groupId>org.ops4j.gaderian</groupId>
                         <artifactId>gaderian</artifactId>
                         <version>${project.version}</version>
                       </dependency>
                       
                      <dependency>
                        <groupId>org.ops4j.gaderian</groupId>
                        <artifactId>gaderian-util</artifactId>
                        <version>${project.version}</version>
                      </dependency>
                       
                       ....
                    </dependencies>]]>
            </source>

            <subsection name="Using Snapshots">
                <p>Snapshot versions of Gaderian are available from the OPS4J Maven repository and to use them, please add the following repository information to your pom.xml file:</p>
                <source><![CDATA[
                    ...
                    <repositories>

                        ...

                       <repository>
                          <id>ops4j-repo</id>
                          <name>OPS4J Maven 2 Snapshot Repository</name>
                          <url>http://repository.ops4j.org/mvn-snapshots/</url>
                       </repository>

                       ....

                    </repositories>]]>
                </source>
            </subsection>

        </section>



    </body>
